9.01	Kundalini_syndrome	Kundalini syndrome	A few theorists within the transpersonal field, such as Greyson, refers to this symptomatology as the "Physio-Kundalini syndrome", while other Western academics use the description Kundalini-experience/awakening when describing clinical features related to the concept of Kundalini. Thalbourne describes the term "Kundalini" as "a theoretical construct to explain a syndrome of various psychophysiological and other phenomena...".	
